MAJOR #TBT!!! This is one of the ALDC’s best numbers & most controversial. The 1998 original work went on to be undefeated. The concept 
was taken right from the headlines - young women leaving their newborn babies in a box outside the police station or hospital or even in a public bathroom. Almost a decade later, in 2007 I felt the need to revive it because this horribly sad situation was still going on in our society! Once again this piece went on to cause controversy, open chat rooms, be on top winning, undefeated all over again! 

I always thought I would use it again on the very last episode of Dance Moms. 

This should’ve been the original cast of #dancemoms moms! There mothers were all kind of crazy in their own unique way! Can you spot any #aldcalumni?! Comment below!!!

Thank you @rachel.kreiling original cast!!! !’m Searching for a good clear copy of a 1998 performance!

node.text:
I didn’t post yesterday on July 12th, the anniversary of the dreadful day I began my staycation. I never ever thought things could get any worse - until I was let out. One week later with the most excruciating pain starting in my neck down my back I saw 7 Doctors in 10 days… was even admitted for the first time in my life to a Hospital, yet I was told “Go home, take it easy, you’ll be fine!” On that last day I walked in to get an MRI & never walked out, never walked again! What most don’t know is that I couldn’t go to the doctors that I wanted to, I couldn’t go to the hospital I should’ve gone to, and I was being threatened every day that I would be “sent back” because I was too much trouble, because I was in pain. I even watched the Director of the halfway house tell the paramedics, not to take me to the hospital! 
I thought I was finished with strangers/ male & female “security guards”  screaming in my face for no reason whatsoever - Until last Sat! It just never seems to end. 
Oh, how dramatically  different I dreamed my life was going to be…
